      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;on-language&#34;&gt;On language&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Language has a special role in the universe around us.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Language is inseparable from a set of programs and executions it elicits.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Physical reality is elicited by a language of physical laws.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Biological life is elicited by a language of DNA.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;We spend our lives looking for the language that describes things, and believe it exists.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;GÃ¶del and Kolmogorov say that we can&amp;rsquo;t really find that language,&lt;br&gt;&#xA;but we believe in the fundamental value of the search.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;A neural network is a search procedure for a special case of a language to describe things.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&amp;ldquo;In the beginning was the Word&amp;rdquo; is eerily similar to the description of a system prompt.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
